definition:
ἀνα-στατόω, ῶ
 (ἀνάστατος, driven from home; ἀνίστημι), [in  LXX: Dan.7:23 (דּוּשׁ;* also in Aq., and in π. (see Deiss., LAE, 80 f.; MM, VGT, see word),] 
to stir up, excite, unsettle: with accusative; 
   (a) to tumult and sedition: Act.17:6 21:38; 
   (b) by false teaching: Gal.5:12 (see Milligan, NTD, 73 f.).†
 (AS)
